				<p><p>I think we need 5-3.3 bidirectional voltage shifter (not for camera) to communicate between raspberry pi and create controller, since serial communication protocols for Create uses 0-5 voltage range and Raspberry Pi uses 0-3.3 volt range. This dissimilarity might result in <strong>signal distortion</strong> between the two devices. For instance, raspberry pi might send 2.5V as high signal but in create logic that might not recognize that as  high signal. As you stated,5V might be dangerous for raspberry pi circuit that runs on 3.3V. Also, for <strong>better communication</strong>, I suggest you should build the voltage shifter.</p>
